  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As part of casting this jutsu, you must be able to make contact with a flat surface that could hold a silhouette of a creature of your size. You form hand signs and then touch a surface, placing a large seal on the area, which begins pulling you inside of it. You become a 2D illustration of yourself, your back flush to the wall. Your field of vision is halved to 180 degrees, allowing you to see what is in front and at your sides in the 3D world.</p><p>While in this state, you cannot cast jutsu, but you can move up to your movement speed along the walls, able to go through even the smallest of cracks. You do not make noise and have a chakra signature so faint that only a Sensory jutsu of B-Rank or higher, or True Sight, can detect you. You have advantage on checks to maintain stealth and only have to roll for stealth when you move if a creature could notice you move.</p><p>If a creature would destroy a surface that you are on, this jutsu immediately ends, and you lose hit points equal to the damage dealt to the surface.</p>",
